{"key":"post-13085919","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13085919</id>\n<content>LC has got to be the lamest way on earth to grow mushrooms.&amp;nbsp; If you wish to expand mycelium, grain to grain transfers are at least ten times faster than LC.&amp;nbsp; In addition, you can see and/or smell contamination on grains, something you don't know with liquid culture until you use it, wasting weeks of time when you could have been actually growing healthy mycelium.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Squirting spores into sugar water has about the same odds as putting all your money on the number 13 in Las Vegas at the roulette wheel.&amp;nbsp; If it works, it works well, but when it fails as it usually does, you've lost far more time than if you'd used proper methods.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To answer your question, use soap and water to clean jars.&amp;nbsp; They're going to be sterilized during the next cycle anyway.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13085962</next>\n<prev>13085858</prev>\n<first>13085650</first>\n<last>13087368</last>\n<when>1282494986</when>\n<utime>08/22/10 07:36 PM</utime>\n</post>"}